The Court of Appeal sitting in Makurdi, yesterday, upheld the decision of the governorship election petition tribunal that affirmed the election of Engr. Abdullahi Sule as governor of Nasarawa State. The court, presided over by Justice Jumai Hannatu Sankey, in its judgement, resolved all the five issues raised in the petition brought before it by the PDP and its 2019 governorship candidate, Mr David Emmanuel Ombugadu. The court held that the appellants were unable to prove their case.  Nasarawa governorship: Appeal Court to decide Gov Sule's fate Saturday Appeal court upholds El-Rufai’s election, decides Nasarawa gov’s fate tomorrow Tribunal upholds Sule election as Nasarawa governor Kindly take one minute (1) of your time to fill out this short question. This questionnaire is designed to sample readers' opinions regarding what the feel about Daily Trust newspaper advertisement; it is not intended to used for any purpose other than to improve the quality of our newspapers. Any information provided will therefore be treated as confidential.